Write a MATLAB code to simulate the vibration technique for detecting oxide scale cracking, where the resonant frequency decreases with continued cracking and increases with oxide repair.

```matlab
% Define the initial resonant frequency
f_initial = 1000; % Hz

% Define the rate of frequency decrease with oxide cracking
cracking_rate = 0.1; % Hz per crack

% Define the number of cracks
num_cracks = 10;

% Define the rate of frequency increase with oxide repair
repair_rate = 0.2; % Hz per repair

% Define the number of repairs
num_repairs = 5;

% Simulate the effect of oxide cracking on resonant frequency
f_cracked = f_initial;
for i = 1:num_cracks
    f_cracked = f_cracked - cracking_rate;
end

% Simulate the effect of oxide repair on resonant frequency
f_repaired = f_cracked;
for i = 1:num_repairs
    f_repaired = f_repaired + repair_rate;
end

% Plot the results
figure;
plot([f_initial f_cracked f_repaired]);
xlabel('Event');
ylabel('Resonant Frequency (Hz)');
legend('Initial', 'After Cracking', 'After Repair');
```

